# 🧱 HUNT PERSISTENCE + VERSIONING ENGINE (FINAL PLATFORM LAYER)

## 🧠 CORE IDEA

A hunt is not a file.

It is:

# a versioned data lineage graph over time

Meaning:

* every change has history
* every published state is immutable
* every schema upgrade is traceable

---

# 🧱 1. THREE-LAYER STORAGE MODEL

```txt id="pv0"
DRAFT STATE  →  WORKING EDITABLE VERSION
PUBLISHED    →  IMMUTABLE PLAYER VERSION
ARCHIVE      →  HISTORY / SNAPSHOTS
```

---

## 🟡 DRAFT STATE (CREATOR WORKSPACE)

* constantly changing
* autosaved
* unsafe by design
* supports undo/redo

Stored as:

```json id="pv1"
{
  "huntId": "demo",
  "version": "draft",
  "state": { }
}
```

---

## 🟢 PUBLISHED STATE (PLAYER RUNTIME)

* frozen snapshot
* cannot be mutated
* used by GameRuntime only

```json id="pv2"
{
  "huntId": "demo",
  "version": 3,
  "publishedAt": 1710000000,
  "state": { }
}
```

---

## 🔵 ARCHIVE STATE (HISTORY)

* all previous versions
* used for rollback, comparison, audit

```json id="pv3"
{
  "huntId": "demo",
  "versions": [1, 2, 3]
}
```

---

# 🧱 2. VERSION MODEL (CORE RULE)

Every publish increments version:

```txt id="pv4"
draft → publish → v1
draft → publish → v2
draft → publish → v3
```

---

## 🧠 RULE

## Published hunts are immutable forever

No edits. No exceptions.

Only:

* clone
* fork
* new version

---

# 🧱 3. SAVE SYSTEM (COMMAND-BASED PERSISTENCE)

All persistence is driven by your command system.

---

## AUTO-SAVE COMMAND

```json id="pv5"
{
  "type": "persist.autosave",
  "payload": {
    "huntId": "demo",
    "state": "draft"
  }
}
```

Triggered every:

* node edit
* edge change
* asset assignment
* effect update

---

## MANUAL SAVE (FORCED SNAPSHOT)

```json id="pv6"
{
  "type": "persist.saveSnapshot",
  "payload": {
    "label": "before boss redesign"
  }
}
```

---

# 🧱 4. PUBLISH PIPELINE (CRITICAL FLOW)

This is your “launch button”.

---

## FLOW:

```txt id="pv7"
Validate Draft
   ↓
Run Schema Migration Check
   ↓
Freeze State Snapshot
   ↓
Assign Version Number
   ↓
Store in Published Registry
   ↓
Lock Runtime Input
```

---

## PUBLISH COMMAND

```json id="pv8"
{
  "type": "persist.publish",
  "payload": {
    "huntId": "demo",
    "notes": "First playable version"
  }
}
```

---

# 🧱 5. SCHEMA VERSIONING SYSTEM (VERY IMPORTANT)

This is what protects you long-term.

---

## SCHEMA VERSION TRACKING

```json id="pv9"
{
  "huntSchemaVersion": 1,
  "engineVersion": "V3.0.0"
}
```

---

## WHY THIS MATTERS

When you evolve the engine:

* nodes change shape
* effects expand
* rules evolve

Without versioning → old hunts break

---

# 🧱 6. MIGRATION ENGINE (CRITICAL FUTURE SAFETY SYSTEM)

When schema updates happen:

---

## MIGRATION FLOW:

```txt id="pv10"
oldVersion → migration function → newVersion
```

---

## EXAMPLE:

```js id="pv11"
function migrate_v1_to_v2(hunt) {
  return {
    ...hunt,
    nodes: migrateNodes(hunt.nodes)
  };
}
```

---

## RULE

Every schema change MUST include:

* migration function
* backward compatibility path

---

# 🧱 7. DIFF SYSTEM (POWERFUL CREATOR FEATURE)

Used for:

* version comparison
* undo auditing
* collaboration

---

## DIFF MODEL:

```json id="pv12"
{
  "added": [],
  "removed": [],
  "modified": []
}
```

---

## EXAMPLE USE CASE

* “What changed since last publish?”
* “Why did this node break?”
* “Compare version 2 vs 3”

---

# 🧱 8. CLONE / FORK SYSTEM

Creators never overwrite published hunts.

They:

## CLONE → new draft

```json id="pv13"
{
  "type": "persist.clone",
  "payload": {
    "fromVersion": 3,
    "newHuntId": "demo-fork"
  }
}
```

---

# 🧱 9. RECOVERY SYSTEM (CRASH SAFETY)

Auto-recovery from draft snapshots:

* last valid state
* last autosave
* last command batch

---

## RULE

No creator work is ever lost.

---

